<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-227-123 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 394 484</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Feb 4 1991 v8 n5 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple requests exclusive spectrum for wireless LANs.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Messmer, Ellen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple Computer Inc seeks an exclusive radio spectrum forwireless-local area networks from the Federal CommunicationsCommission (FCC).andP;  Apple wants the FCC to set aside 40 MHz ofbandwidth in the 1,850-to-1,990 MHz band to expand US investmentin the development of wireless LAN products.andP;  Apple seeksregulations prohibiting other users or service providers fromgaining an exclusive license to the 40 MHz requested for awireless LAN.andP;  Private microwave users at utilities, petroleumcompanies and railroads regard Apple's petition as a threat.andP;  Aspokesman for Utilities Telecommunications Council claims 100 gas,water and electric utilities have fixed, operational microwavesystems valued at half a billion dollars in the band Apple wantsto use.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Political activity).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Topic:     Wireless NetworksRadio FrequencyGovernment RegulationUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionMicrowave CommunicationsUser Needs.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>